title: Despite Drone Flyover, Saints Sweep 'Jackets
text:
Despite Drone Flyover, Saints Sweep 'Jackets 
By Zach Schneider October 14, 2015 Updated Oct 14, 2015 at 7:10 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- A momentary delay because of a drone flying overhead wasn't enough to distract the St. Scholastica women's soccer team from the business at hand on Wednesday afternoon, and that ended in a 4-0 win over Twin Ports rival UW-Superior. 
Kirsten Olson scored the game's first goal early in the first half, with that coming before was delayed a few minutes while officials waited for a drone that was flying overhead the field to clear the area.

Becca Rancour and Jill Rosby then both scored goals in the second part of the first half for the Saints, with Duluth, Minn. native Leah Hamm adding another in the second half. 
Kelsey Reeves made one save to earn the shutout for the Saints, while Bailey Henderson finished with six saves for the Yellowjackets. 
St. Scholastica is now (7-6-2) overall this season, while UW-Superior drops to (2-9-0).
